<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-07-11T11:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-07-11T11:44:00-05:00" n="300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/43: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Legation in Liberia</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-11T16:00:00-00:44">July 11, 1929—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>33. Department’s telegram 13, June 22, 2 p.m. Barber Line representative,
                            Monrovia, states that to date he has not received any instructions from
                            his principals and there have been no shipments on his vessels since May
                            14th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>